The paper deals with communication tasks in networks, which are typically studied in the Distributed Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The use of the beeping model, which is a simple and weak communication model, suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Networked and Internet Systems (cs.NI) sub-category. The algorithms presented in the paper involve efficient message passing and information dissemination, which are topics of interest in the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category. The paper also involves the study of network properties such as diameter and size, which are relevant to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the analysis of time complexity, which is a topic of interest in the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category.
